BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:QaG8G9eedGXbwlRzm7hMs
SUMMARY:Journaling the Garden
DTSTAMP:20260301T153237Z
DTSTART:20260307T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Nature journaling at the Bellevue Botanical Garden is a wonderf
	ul way to connect with the environment through curiosity and observation o
	f the natural world. This free adult program will help guide your practice
	 whether you are just starting out or are an experienced journaler. In thi
	s warm and welcoming environment\, you will be encouraged to experiment an
	d find your voice. In each session we will gather for introductions and br
	ief guidance\, and then head out into Garden to journal and come back toge
	ther to share experiences.   \n\nPlease bring a dedicated journal and some
	thing to write with. We will meet at 9am the first Saturday of January-Nov
	ember 2026. Registration is recommended but not required. REGISTER NOW.  \
	n\nThis free adult program is facilitated by Anne Dziok\, Adult Education 
	Program Manager. Anne is a practicing multi-media artist who shows her wor
	k regionally.    \n\nEmail us  with questions.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity
	.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/17658183/2026-03-07T00\n\nFrom
	 SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/journaling-the-garden/176
	58183/2026-03-07T00
LOCATION:Sharp Cabin\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:nmcOjQrqcZqW1PmV38CCL
SUMMARY:Restoration Event | Pioneer Park
DTSTAMP:20260301T153237Z
DTSTART:20260307T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy the towering trees\, listen to the birds\, and give a lit
	tle back to this beautiful park by removing common ivy that is taking over
	  the understory of Pioneer Park's SE quadrant. It will be a great chance 
	t o get your hands in the dirt\, learn about native plants and our local f
	orests\, and work alongside neighbors and friends!\n\nAll ages welcome\, a
	nd no experience necessary! Gloves\, tools\, water\, and small snacks prov
	ided. Please note: we require participants aged 14 and under to volunteer 
	 with a parent or guardian at a ratio of 1 adult to 3 kids.\n\nWhen: Satur
	d ay\, March 7th\, 10am-1pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park SE\, follow volunteer e
	vent signs\n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in clothes you don't mi
	nd get ting dirty \\(think: long pants\, boots or sneakers\\). Bring water
	. Small snacks\, gloves\, and tools will be provided.\n\nRegistration: htt
	ps://volunteersignup.org/CWRCR\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/de
	tails/restoration-event-pioneer-park/18066420/2026-03-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtod
	ay - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/restoration-event-pioneer
	-park/18066420/2026-03-07T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
